c6 Qg4+ 1/2-1/2 With Chess:Pgn you will find a game by $game->date or $game->game. For our last example we will have $game->date : "????.??.??" $game->game : "1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Nf6 4.Ng5 d5 5.exd5 Nxd5 6.Nxf7 Kxf7 7.Qf3+ Ke6 8.Nc3 Ne7 9.O-O c6 10.Re1 Bd7 11.d4 Kd6 12.Rxe5 Ng6 13.Nxd5 Nxe5 14.dxe5+ Kc5 15.Qa3+ Kxc4 16.Qd3+ Kc5 17.b4# 1-0" The module provide a good set of tools to modify PGN File but you will have to make yourself the while :)','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 218,'pod' => 145,'total' => 363,'with_comments' => 1},'releases' => 1,'size' => {'packed' => 4950,'unpacked' => 16850},'testers' => {'pass' => 7},'uses' => ['5.004','Exporter','warnings']},'ChildExit_0-1.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'TQISJIM','description' => 'alt Apache::Registry END block handler','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 83,'pod' => 96,'total' => 179,'with_comments' => 8},'releases' => 1,'size' => {'packed' => 4854,'unpacked' => 10901},'testers' => {'pass' => 3},'uses' => ['5.006','Carp','DynaLoader','Exporter','strict','warnings']},'Chipcard-CTAPI-0.2.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'WHOM','description' => 'Communication with chipcard terminals','files' => ['Makefile.PL','README','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 930,'pod' => 580,'total' => 1510,'with_comments' => 163},'releases' => 2,'size' => {'packed' => 29281,'unpacked' => 119156},'testers' => {},'uses' => ['5.005','AutoLoader','Carp','Exporter','Fcntl','XSLoader','strict','warnings']},'CircuitLayout-0.04.tar.gz' => {'author' => 'SCHUMACK','description' => undef,'files' => ['README','Build.PL','META.yml','MANIFEST'],'lines' => {'nonpod' => 2265,'pod' => 441,'total' => 2706,'with_comments' => 288},'releases' => 2,'size' => {'packed' => 13502,'unpacked' => 76130},'testers' => {},'uses' => ['5.006','CircuitLayout::Boundary','CircuitLayout::Coord','CircuitLayout::Edge','CircuitLayout::Rectangle','CircuitLayout::Text','Math::Trig','Tk','Tk::WorldCanvas','strict']},